President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring May 6-12, 2018 as National Charter Schools Week. The proclamation celebrates the growth of charter schools in the United States, with 44 states, the District of Columbia, and Puerto Rico passing laws authorizing their creation. The President emphasizes the importance of charter schools in providing high-quality education options and promoting accountability, innovation, and academic achievement. He also calls on states and communities to support and empower parents and families by endorsing high-quality charter schools as a school choice option. The President's administration has prioritized support for charter schools, including increasing funding for the Federal Charter Schools Program. The proclamation recognizes the role of charter schools in providing rigorous education and preparing students for the challenges of the 21st century.